    Introduction to Constrained KDE

    Predict density and moments using the fitted constrained KDE model

    predict_constrained_kde.Rd

    Predict density and moments using the fitted constrained KDE model

    Usage

    predict_constrained_kde(model, x_seq)

    Arguments

    model

    The fitted model object

    x_seq

    The sequence of points to estimate the density

    Value

    A list containing density estimates and first four moments

    Examples

    set.seed(42)
n <- 100
x <- c(rnorm(0.5*n, 0, 1), rnorm(0.5 * n, 1.5, 1/3))
h <- 0.6
model <- fit_constrained_kde(x, h)
x_seq <- seq(min(x) - 1, max(x) + 1, length.out = 1000)
predictions <- predict_constrained_kde(model, x_seq)
print(predictions$density)
